Topic of Interest

  • Do individuals correctly/rationally predict future preferences?

Design

  • 120 Students/Staff from UC Berkeley
  • Control group and treated (incentivised) group
  • Use card swipe data to show attendance (but not duration)

Timeline

Elicitation

  • Problem trying to incentivize people to predict their future behavior
    • Example: wake up time
  • Solution: The p-Coupon:

Coupons

  • Randomised over the 5 target weeks and values of 1, 2, 3, 5, 7
  • 4 per subject (leaving one week with no coupon)
  • Solicited WTP for coupon and how many times subject would attend, should they hold the coupon
  • At the end of the third meeting, subjects received one coupon at random
